# Canonical source: https://sti.nasa.gov/docs/thesaurus/thesaurus-SKOS.xml (66 MB SKOS/RDF-XML)
# Ontology IRI:    https://sti.nasa.gov/docs/thesaurus/thesaurus-SKOS.xml
# Retrieved:       SEE ontologies-manifest.json
# License:         Public domain (NASA STI Program)
#
# shepard-bundled stub of the NASA Thesaurus (~18,400 terms). This file contains a
# curated excerpt of ~110 concepts covering propulsion, combustion, test engineering,
# cryogenic fluids, measurement, and structural/materials topics relevant to
# liquid-propellant rocket engine research (the LUMEN showcase domain).
#
# Concept IRIs use fragment identifiers that match the termID fields in the canonical
# SKOS/RDF-XML source so that a full import via `shepard-admin semantic refresh-ontologies`
# (using n10s.rdf.import.fetch) produces the same :Resource URIs as this stub and
# deduplicates cleanly.
#
# Operators wanting the full 18,400-term NASA Thesaurus run:
#   shepard-admin semantic refresh-ontologies   (downloads from canonicalUrl, re-imports)
# or import the SKOS XML directly via the admin UI (Semantic Repositories → Upload).

@base <https://sti.nasa.gov/docs/thesaurus/thesaurus-SKOS.xml> .
@prefix rdf:   <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs:  <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix owl:   <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix skos:  <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .

<> a owl:Ontology ;
   dcterms:title "NASA Thesaurus (shepard-bundled propulsion stub)"@en ;
   rdfs:label    "NASA Thesaurus"@en ;
   rdfs:comment  "Controlled vocabulary of the NASA Scientific and Technical Information Program. This file is a curated stub of the aerospace propulsion / test engineering subset."@en .

